  "description": "This dinner keeps the palate warm and savory while leaning on vegetables and lentils more than fat. Thinai Vegetable Kanji brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Combine the grain, moong dal, vegetable, salt, and water in a pot and bring to a boil over high heat.",
    "Reduce to low heat and cook covered for 18 to 20 minutes, stirring twice, until the mixture turns soft and porridge-like.",
    "Heat oil in a small pan, add cumin, pepper, and ginger, and cook on medium heat for 30 seconds. Stir into the kanji.",
    "Cool for 2 minutes, then fold in the buttermilk for a softer finish before serving."
  ],
